label: identifier
comment: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing, such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See background notes for more details.
subproperties: http://schema.org/accountId, http://schema.org/confirmationNumber, http://schema.org/duns, http://schema.org/flightNumber, http://schema.org/globalLocationNumber, http://schema.org/gtin12, http://schema.org/gtin13, http://schema.org/gtin14, http://schema.org/gtin8, http://schema.org/isbn, http://schema.org/issn, http://schema.org/legislationIdentifier, http://schema.org/leiCode, http://schema.org/orderNumber, http://schema.org/productID, http://schema.org/serialNumber, http://schema.org/sku, http://schema.org/taxID

label: name
comment: The name of the item.

label: alternateName
comment: An alias for the item.

label: description
comment: A description of the item.

label: url
comment: URL of the item.

label: sameAs
comment: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

label: image
comment: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

label: location
comment: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.
subproperties: http://schema.org/course, http://schema.org/entertainmentBusiness, http://schema.org/exerciseCourse, http://schema.org/foodEstablishment, http://schema.org/foodEvent, http://schema.org/fromLocation, http://schema.org/homeLocation, http://schema.org/sportsActivityLocation, http://schema.org/sportsEvent, http://schema.org/toLocation, http://schema.org/workLocation

label: logo
comment: An associated logo.

label: givenName
comment: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person. This can be used along with familyName instead of the name property.

label: additionalName
comment: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

label: familyName
comment: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of an Person. This can be used along with givenName instead of the name property.

label: jobTitle
comment: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

label: endDate
comment: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

label: startDate
comment: The start date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

label: price
comment:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

  • Use the priceCurrency property (with standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

label: priceCurrency
comment:
The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

label: learningResourceType
comment: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

label: license
comment: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

label: datePublished
comment: Date of first broadcast/publication.

label: version
comment: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

label: review
comment: A review of the item.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/Brand, http://schema.org/CreativeWork, http://schema.org/Event, http://schema.org/Offer, http://schema.org/Organization, http://schema.org/Place, http://schema.org/Product, http://schema.org/Service

label: thumbnailUrl
comment: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

label: timeRequired
comment: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

label: ratingCount
comment: The count of total number of ratings.

label: ratingValue
comment: The rating for the content.

label: worstRating
comment: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

label: bestRating
comment: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

label: text
comment: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

label: transcript
comment: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

label: thumbnail
comment: Thumbnail image for an image or video.

label: contentSize
comment: File size in (mega/kilo) bytes.

label: contentUrl
comment: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

label: encodingFormat
comment:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).

In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

label: width
comment: The width of the item.

label: height
comment: The height of the item.

label: duration
comment: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/Audiobook, http://schema.org/Event, http://schema.org/MediaObject, http://schema.org/Movie, http://schema.org/MusicRecording, http://schema.org/MusicRelease, http://schema.org/QuantitativeValueDistribution

label: comment
comment: Comments, typically from users.

label: audience
comment: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/CreativeWork, http://schema.org/Event, http://schema.org/LodgingBusiness, http://schema.org/PlayAction, http://schema.org/Product, http://schema.org/Service

label: aggregateRating
comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/Brand, http://schema.org/CreativeWork, http://schema.org/Event, http://schema.org/Offer, http://schema.org/Organization, http://schema.org/Place, http://schema.org/Product, http://schema.org/Service

label: inLanguage
comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

label: subtitleLanguage
comment: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in IETF BCP 47 standard format.

label: offers
comment: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/AggregateOffer, http://schema.org/CreativeWork, http://schema.org/Event, http://schema.org/MenuItem, http://schema.org/Product, http://schema.org/Service, http://schema.org/Trip

label: genre
comment: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

label: provider
comment: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/CreativeWork, http://schema.org/Invoice, http://schema.org/ParcelDelivery, http://schema.org/Reservation, http://schema.org/Service, http://schema.org/Trip

label: member
comment: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

label: memberOf
comment: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

label: author
comment: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

label: instructor
comment: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the CourseInstance.

label: isPartOf
comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

label: hasPart
comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

label: dateIndexed
comment: Date of first appearance of resource on TCC Web Portal, which is the interface to interact with ERuDIte resources and materials

label: enables
comment: Indicates that the mastery/completion of a work can enable understanding of another. Similar to schema:coursePrerequisites, but at the CreativeWork level.

label: provides
comment: Indicates that an Organization provides a CreativeWork.

label: syllabus
comment: Captures the syllabus text (i.e. the order and structure in which concepts are taught) for a Course.
